This paper deals with the design of wireless sensor networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and heuristics to solve optimization problems, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Algorithmic Complexity (cs.AL). The paper also involves the use of information theory to ensure QoS, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of survivable network design, which involves the use of control systems and decision-making algorithms, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
